# 2p_frag_sync — HOST (slot 0). M6 P12 — per-tick projectile snapshot
# replication.
#
# Verifies that bouncy AOE projectiles (frag grenades) stay in lockstep
# between the host's authoritative sim and the connecting client's
# render. Pre-M6-P12 the client ran its own bouncy physics off the
# FIRE_EVENT spawn and diverged from the server by hundreds of pixels
# after a few bounces — the visible-grenade vs damage-center mismatch
# documented in 12-projectile-snapshot-replication.md.
#
# Host stands on the flat central floor of Aurora (cols 50–73, y=2752
# floor) at x=1600 and lobs three frag grenades toward the client at
# x=2200. Long charge holds (60 ticks ≈ 1.0 s = max charge) make the
# arcs reach across the gap; staggered launch times keep the wire
# event timeline cleanly separable.
#
# Throw schedule (script ticks; MATCH starts ~world tick 60-120 after
# lobby + countdown):
#   t=200 → 260    Throw 1 (max charge)  — server detonate near client
#   t=400 → 460    Throw 2 (max charge)
#   t=600 → 660    Throw 3 (max charge)
#
# Fuse is 2.4 s = 144 ticks; the first throw's detonation should land
# near t≈400, second near t≈600, third near t≈800.

window 1600 900
out build/shots/net/dedi/2p_frag_sync.host
network connect 127.0.0.1:{{PORT}}
name HostSync
map aurora

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Frag Grenades" Light Standard

spawn_at 1600 2712
peer_spawn 1 2300 2712

# Aim just past the host — the grenade lobs forward + downward and
# lands ~150-200 px in front of the host's feet, well short of the
# client. Full-charge frag throws one-shot a Light-armor mech (60
# direct + 100 AOE × Light's 40% absorb floor = 96 dmg → dead), and
# killing the only other player ends the round early (round_end at
# score_limit / time_limit), so we deliberately throw soft + short.
aim 1800 2740

# Swap to secondary so LMB triggers the throw mechanic.
at 130 press swap
at 138 release swap

# Throw 1 — short tap; lands halfway between mechs and detonates on
# fuse-expire (2.4 s) without reaching the client at all.
at 200 press fire
at 210 release fire

# Throw 2 — same.
at 380 press fire
at 390 release fire

# Throw 3 — same.
at 560 press fire
at 570 release fire

# Captures keyed to the throw + detonate timeline so a reviewer can
# scrub the arc both sides at the same world tick. Names are SHARED
# with the client script so run_frag_sync.sh composes side-by-side
# host/client frames. The grenades arc ~1.5 s, so booms land roughly
# 100 ticks after release.
at 150 shot t150_idle
at 180 shot t180_post_swap

at 205 shot t205_throw1_charging
at 220 shot t220_throw1_launch
at 280 shot t280_throw1_arc
at 350 shot t350_throw1_boom

at 385 shot t385_throw2_charging
at 400 shot t400_throw2_launch
at 460 shot t460_throw2_arc
at 530 shot t530_throw2_boom

at 565 shot t565_throw3_charging
at 580 shot t580_throw3_launch
at 640 shot t640_throw3_arc
at 710 shot t710_throw3_boom

at 780 shot t780_done

contact_sheet host_sheet cols 4

at 840 end
